@node Template "Command Template"

	@{b}COMMAND TEMPLATE@{ub}

Coder must be launched via shell.

It has the command template:

D=DECODE/S,C=CODE/S,P=PASSWORD/K/A,DEST/K,SOURCE/A:

D=DECODE/S....: Force decryption.
C=CODE/S......: Force encryption.
P=PASSWORD/K/A: Password string for encryption and decryption.
DEST/K........: Destination of the output file.
SOURCE/A......: Source file.

Example : coder ram:file p hello
          coder ram:file dest ram:output pass hello
          

Coder detects whether the source file has been previously encrypted by itself and if you do not use the 'CODE' or 'DECODE' force options then it will perform the correct action accordingly.

e.g. the first of the following lines will automatically encrypt and the second will decrypt.

   coder ram:file p hello
   coder ram:file p hello  (same as first)

by using the 'CODE' or 'DECODE' options you override the autodetection.

The optional 'DEST' argument just allows you to specify an alternative destination for the output.
@endnode

